{"key":"post-7557009","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7557009</id>\n<content>I use rubber side up so the lids don't get stuck to the glass.  I've never left the rings loose, always tightening them fully.  With pf jars it doesn't matter because the verm on top is the filter, but with grains and filters, you should tighten the lids so contaminants don't have a chance to get under the filter after sterilization.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>7556945</prev>\n<first>7554542</first>\n<last>7557009</last>\n<when>1193281630</when>\n<utime>10/25/07 06:07 AM</utime>\n</post>"}